      <p>One of the most critical pieces of information on any medicine package is the expiration date. In Italy, this is typically displayed as "Scad." or "Scadenza" followed by a date. You'll often see it written as "EXP" or "Scad." followed by MM/YY format. Never use a medication after this date, as its effectiveness and safety cannot be guaranteed.</p>

