    <p>If your doctor determines medication is necessary, they'll issue a prescription—either ricetta rossa (if you're SSN-registered) or ricetta bianca (for private patients). The prescription will include medication name, dosage, quantity, and instructions. Some doctors write prescriptions by hand; others use electronic systems generating official prescription documents.</p>
