    <p>Ricetta rossa is the SSN-covered prescription system requiring only €5-€10 copay regardless of medication cost. Ricetta bianca is the private prescription system requiring full pharmaceutical price payment. Ricetta rossa requires SSN registration and covers formulary-listed medications. Ricetta bianca is available to anyone through any licensed physician. The cost difference between systems is dramatic—ricetta rossa enables affordable chronic medication management for SSN-registered residents. Electronic prescriptions are increasingly standard in Italy, registered in national databases. Paper prescriptions remain valid and are still commonly used. Most Italian medications are covered by ricetta rossa when medically appropriate. Prescription refills and multiple fills reduce doctor office visits when authorized. Validity dates, quantity restrictions, and controlled substance regulations apply to Italian prescriptions. Understanding your prescription type helps estimate medication costs and plan healthcare accordingly.</p>

