    <p>Common emergencies include severe toothaches (often indicating deep decay or infection), broken teeth from trauma, and knockedout teeth. For knocked-out teeth, rinse with saline solution (don't scrub), keep moist, and seek immediate emergency dental care—teeth can sometimes be replanted if treated quickly.</p>
