    <p>After receiving vaccinations in Italy, you'll receive a vaccination certificate (certificato vaccinale) documenting the vaccines administered. This certificate is important for school enrollment, employment, travel, and healthcare purposes. The European vaccination certificate is now standard and includes QR codes for digital verification. Keep multiple copies of your vaccination certificate in both paper and digital formats.</p>
